1
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:00,920
You're here alone with my husband?

2
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,960
How shameless!

3
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,160
Calm down, Prao.

4
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,680
If you maintained your relationship well,

5
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,440
no one could take him from you.

6
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,120
<i>Saifah?</i>

7
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,400
Yes, he's Saifah, my eldest son.

8
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:14,280
Where'd you find this photo?

9
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,760
Please take me there!

10
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,360
- Ms. Narin. Please calm down.
- Ms. Mook.

11
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,440
Ms. Mook.

12
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,200
Ms. Narin, what's wrong? Ms. Narin!

13
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,200
Help! Somebody help!

14
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,920
You have to marry Bell only.

15
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,320
No,

16
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:31,000
I won't do what I don't want to anymore.

17
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,560
Stop right there, Thee.

18
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:38,560
If you walk out now,
you'll be left with nothing.

19
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,000
Why are you telling me this?

20
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:44,200
That woman's got nothing to do with me.

21
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,320
Saifah!

22
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,800
I learned all about you from Mr. Pitak.

23
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,760
And I also

24
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:22,160
learned about Saifah from Ms. Narin.

25
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,480
What are you talking about?

26
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:36,560
You're the only family Ms. Narin has left.

27
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:41,720
That's why I rushed here to tell you
before it's all too late.

28
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,960
Mr. Thee,

29
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,040
are you okay?

30
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,040
If you were me, would you feel okay

31
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,640
with the fact that your mom left you

32
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,160
and orphaned you as a child?

33
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:22,440
Are you that angry with Ms. Narin?

34
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:29,440
That woman needs to pay
for what she did to me and my brother.

35
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,160
Can't you see?

36
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:37,520
I still haven't done anything,
yet she's already dying.

37
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,000
I guess karma is real.

38
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,520
Mr. Thee!

39
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:51,280
- Come on, let's do it.
- Wait, bro.

40
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,120
Will it really work?

41
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:58,040
Of course! Those deadbeats
always claim they're broke.

42
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:01,360
If we don't threaten them,
they won't pay our boss back,

43
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,000
and he'll chew us out again.

44
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,880
Hey, stop being so scared.

45
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,280
I'm just threatening them,
not killing them.

46
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:16,400
Look, once they wake up and
their entire house smells like gasoline,

47
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,360
they'll know who did it.

48
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:20,640
Then they'll pay
what they owe to end things.

49
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,240
Come on, we gotta hurry,
or someone will see us.

50
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,200
Come on!

51
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,120
- Hurry. Let's go!
- Gosh.

52
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,600
I signed the I.O.U.,
yet you're still scared? Good grief!

53
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,720
I'll pay you back!

54
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:53,280
Wait, where the hell are my cigarettes?

55
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,360
Oh, found 'em.

56
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,280
Ugh.

57
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,040
F-F-Fire!

58
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:23,200
Oh shoot! Fire!

59
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:29,280
Help, help! Somebody help!

60
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,400
Help me put out the fire!

61
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,600
Tawan! Tawan! Get up!

62
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,040
There's a fire! Get up, Tawan!

63
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,520
Let's go, Tawan. Come on.

64
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,280
- My toy car!
- Tawan!

65
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:09,760
Saifah, help me! Help!

66
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,520
Help! Somebody help us!

67
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,800
Saifah, help me!

68
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,480
- There's a fire! Come on. Come here!
- Please help my brother!

69
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,360
Saifah, don't leave me!

70
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:21,080
- We have to run first! Come on!
- Help him first!

71
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,880
Saifah, don't leave me!

72
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,360
I'll come back and save you, Tawan. Tawan!

73
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:28,000
Let go of me!

74
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,720
We can't change the past.

75
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:56,680
Now, we must stay in the present.

76
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:01,080
You're right. We can't change the past,

77
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,480
because Tawan's already dead.

78
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:12,520
But I'll make sure that woman suffers
a thousand times more than we did.

79
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:24,320
I think you should go see Ms. Narin
and let her tell you the truth.

80
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,200
Otherwise,

81
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,280
you may regret it
for the rest of your life.

82
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,200
Please trust me…

83
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:45,640
Mr. Thee.

84
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,680
I can't reach Mr. Thee at all.

85
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,960
Just you wait.

86
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:15,760
If Joe pulls out of the project,
I'll make him pay.

87
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:20,800
Mrs. Anna, I suggest you wait for him
to calm down and then go talk to him.

88
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,880
Why should I have to wait?

89
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,800
I raised him so well.

90
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,920
You could say I changed his life,

91
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,800
or he'd still be an orphan.

92
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:34,880
I've done so much for him,
so he's got to repay me somehow.

93
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:39,720
I did so much for him
that he won't be able to pay it back,

94
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,040
even if he spends his whole life trying.

95
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:46,120
I've been more of a mom
than his mom could ever be,

96
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,520
but look what he's doing to me.

97
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:57,760
Find a way to contact him
and tell him to apologize to me.

98
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,000
Yes, ma'am.

99
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,120
Come on, come on.

100
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,600
Watch. Mine's more powerful.

101
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:45,000
- Check it out, Tawan.
- Wow.

102
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:45,920
Vroom!

103
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:49,360
- See?
- Come on, let's eat.

104
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,560
- Okay, Mom.
- Okay, Mom.

105
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,440
Are you hungry?

106
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,360
- Yes.
- Yes.

107
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:57,840
- For you, Saifah.
- Thanks.

108
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:02,120
For you, Tawan. Okay.

109
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,640
You sure love your omelets, don't you?

110
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,160
Here you go, Mom.

111
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,800
Here you go, Mom.

112
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,680
Thanks, honey. Thank you.

113
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,600
No problem.

114
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,320
Are you hungry?

115
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,040
Is it good?

116
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,800
Yes.

117
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,600
Want some more rice? Yeah?

118
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:40,280
Let's go for seconds. Come on.

119
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,240
- Eat up. Let's see who can eat more.
- I want more.

120
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,640
- Whoever finishes it first wins.
- Okay!

121
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,400
Alright?

122
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:04,720
I'll work hard to earn a lot of money.

123
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:08,760
Next year, I'll send you both to school.

124
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,240
- Okay!
- Okay!

125
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,600
Yeah.

126
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:25,520
Here you go. There's the rest.

127
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,720
Let's hurry, so we can go.

128
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,560
Sir, please give me another month.

129
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,240
I really don't have enough this month.

130
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:47,640
Once I'm paid,
I'll pay your boss right away. Please?

131
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:51,520
- Hell no!
- Please, sir.

132
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,400
How many times have you pushed it back?

133
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:57,880
If you don't pay us in three days,
you're dead!

134
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,400
Three days!

135
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,000
I came like you asked.

136
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:29,640
Can I go now?

137
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,200
Mr. Thee!

138
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,560
Mr. Thee, wait! Mr. Thee!

139
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:38,200
Don't you want to know
why Ms. Narin left you and your brother?

140
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:43,440
Well, do you want to know how much
my brother had to suffer before he died?

141
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:48,480
Honestly, there's someone
who should've died instead of him.

142
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,280
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

143
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:10,360
- Hell no!
- Please, sir.

144
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:22,600
Saifah, take good care
of your little brother, okay?

145
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,080
Keep the door locked.

146
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,840
Don't open it for anyone.

147
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:28,000
What if it's those two guys?

148
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:30,360
Just don't open it for anyone.

149
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:33,680
Wait till I get home. Do you understand?

150
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:34,720
Yes, Mom.

151
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:38,960
Good. I'll buy you
some delicious food, okay?

152
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,560
- Okay.
- Okay.

153
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,960
Good boys.

154
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,760
- Look out for each other, okay?
- Okay.

155
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,280
Bye.

156
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,480
Keep it closed. Don't go anywhere.

157
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:01,440
Okay.

158
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,600
<i>Don't you want to know</i>
<i>why Ms. Narin left you and your brother?</i>

159
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:32,520
Well, do you want to know how much
my brother had to suffer before he died?

160
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:37,000
<i>We can't change the past.</i>

161
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,880
<i>We must stay in the present.</i>

162
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,800
You're right. We can't change the past,

163
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:46,240
because Tawan's already dead.

164
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,000
Saifah, help me!

165
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,680
- There's a fire! Come on. Come here!
- Please help my brother!

166
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,600
No! Let go of me!

167
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:23,800
Ms. Narin.

168
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,760
Ms. Narin?

169
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,120
Ms. Mook?

170
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,320
Yes, it's me.

171
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:46,960
How could you do it to us?

172
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,080
How could you leave us?

173
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,120
- Mr. Thee! Mr. Thee!
- Tell me!

174
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:56,320
- Tell me! How could you?!
- Mr. Thee, please stop it.

175
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,120
Calm down, would you?

176
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,320
- Mr. Thee!
- Do you have any idea

177
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,680
how much we had to suffer?!

178
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,520
How could you leave your own kids?!

179
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,280
- Mr. Thee!
- How could you?!

180
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:09,240
Mr. Thee, please stop it! Mr. Thee!

181
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:13,040
Ms. Narin! Ms. Narin?

182
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,880
Help! Please help her!

183
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:21,320
Doctor! Nurse! She's having a seizure!

184
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,680
Over here!

185
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:26,720
Please help her! Please help Ms. Narin.

186
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,040
Mr. Thee…

187
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:53,000
After the collectors came
to collect her debts that day…

188
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,880
…Ms. Narin tried to find a job.

189
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,240
But unfortunately,

190
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,160
she got hit by a car

191
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,400
and had a severe concussion,

192
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:11,120
which led to temporary memory loss.

193
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,840
But as soon as she recovered,

194
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,080
she began looking
for you and your brother.

195
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:22,400
But your house was destroyed by the fire,

196
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:26,120
and she never heard about you two again.

197
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:45,520
Ms. Narin never meant to leave you two
like you think she did.

198
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:49,080
She's been looking for you
and your brother all along.

199
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:16,760
Doctor?

200
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,280
She's stable now.

201
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,880
She has coronary artery disease.

202
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:25,320
For now, I've given her medication
to treat the symptoms.

203
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,600
But most importantly, during this period,

204
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:30,680
please make sure
nothing causes her distress.

205
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,640
Thank you.

206
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,920
I can't believe Mr. Thee
is Ms. Narin's actual son.

207
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:03,440
If I hadn't heard it from her,

208
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,280
I wouldn't have believed it either.

209
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:09,240
I just feel so bad for Mr. Thee.

210
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:12,080
He's been carrying
that hatred for his mother

211
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:14,560
without knowing the truth.

212
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,280
You're right.

213
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:23,120
He has suffered a lot.

214
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:26,640
He lost his brother,

215
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:29,040
and his mother disappeared
at the same time.

216
00:21:30,760 --> 00:21:33,280
But I feel bad for Ms. Narin too, Mom.

217
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:37,520
Well, where's Mr. Thee now?

218
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,640
He's looking after her at the hospital.

219
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,560
I have work, so I had to leave early.

220
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:47,040
- Kongkwan.
- Good morning, Mommy.

221
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:50,520
Last night, you came home late,
so I didn't get to see you at all.

222
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,760
I'm sorry.

223
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:56,800
Last night, something urgent came up,
so I was home late.

224
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:57,920
It's okay.

225
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:03,400
Mommy, when will you bring Thee
to see me again?

226
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:05,520
I miss him.

227
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,400
Let's eat first, shall we?

228
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,680
Come on. Before it gets cold.

229
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,200
Can you eat by yourself?
Need me to feed you?

230
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,240
You can? Okay.

231
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,320
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

232
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:06,000
Ms. Mook left you breakfast.

233
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,400
Thank you.

234
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:22,080
<i>I have a meeting this morning.</i>

235
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:24,160
<i>You were sleeping,</i>
<i>so I didn't want to disturb you.</i>

236
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:28,280
<i>Please eat something,</i>
<i>or you'll get sick too.</i>

237
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:10,680
Here I am!
Where should I take you, Mr. Passenger?

238
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,800
- Hop on!
- To the market, please.

239
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:15,440
- To the market? Okay.
- That way, please, Mr. Motorcycle Taxi.

240
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,480
Let's go, bro.

241
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,040
<i>Go around! Faster!</i>

242
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,280
Hey!

243
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,600
Come on, hurry. Faster!

244
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,920
- Come here.
- Come on!

245
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:43,760
- Why are you so fast?
- I am.

246
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:47,800
- Oh no.
- Quick. Here I come!

247
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,960
Faster! Do a zigzag!

248
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,720
- Here I go.
- How'd you get through?

249
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,880
There!

250
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:26,000
The car got wrecked.

251
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,040
- No!
- Boom!

252
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,120
I'm sorry, Mom.

253
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:17,320
Mr. Thee.

254
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:27,640
It's me, Saifah.

255
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,040
What are you talking about?

256
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:35,320
You know Saifah too?

257
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:43,880
I'm Saifah, Mom. I'm your son.

258
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:52,840
That day, you told me and my brother

259
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:56,560
you were going to get us some food.

260
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,400
You told us to wait.

261
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:04,160
So we waited.

262
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:09,760
But you never came back.

263
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:15,360
I'll buy you some delicious food, okay?

264
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:17,920
- Okay.
- Good boys.

265
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:21,800
- Look out for each other, okay?
- Okay.

266
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:22,720
Bye.

267
00:28:29,520 --> 00:28:31,320
Keep it closed. Don't go anywhere.

268
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:49,920
Saifah, is that really you, honey?

269
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:53,320
Saifah, I'm sorry, honey. I'm sorry!

270
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:56,120
Saifah…

271
00:28:56,840 --> 00:29:00,360
I've missed you so bad, Saifah.

272
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:05,040
Saifah… I'm so sorry.

273
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,800
At first, I was really angry with you

274
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,680
for leaving us.

275
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:24,280
But now I know. I know.

276
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,880
I know what you've had to go through.

277
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,520
I'm so sorry.

278
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:34,680
- No. It's okay.
- I'm so sorry.

279
00:29:34,760 --> 00:29:37,400
I'm sorry for not coming home
to you sooner.

280
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:42,000
- Mom, it's okay. Really.
- I'm really sorry.

281
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:44,680
It's okay.

282
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:47,240
How about Tawan, honey? Did he come too?

283
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:50,360
Is your brother here too? Is he?

284
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:52,000
Where is he?

285
00:29:57,320 --> 00:30:01,440
Mom, look, you should get some rest first.

286
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,680
- Okay.
- Get some rest, okay?

287
00:30:05,520 --> 00:30:08,200
The doctor wants you to get
lots of rest, so you won't feel tired.

288
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,520
I'm so glad to meet you, honey.

289
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,600
I've missed you.

290
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,280
Mook, did you see the email?

291
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,520
What email?

292
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:37,240
The One mailed us
a contract termination letter.

293
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:38,240
What?

294
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,080
THE ONE HOTEL
EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT TERMINATION LETTER

295
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,360
DEAR A ROUND TRIP TRAVEL
WE ARE WRITING TO INFORM YOU

296
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,440
OF THE ONE HOTEL'S INTENT TO TERMINATE
ITS CONTRACT WITH A ROUND TRIP TRAVEL

297
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:48,640
What?

298
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:51,320
Mook.

299
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,280
What happened, Boss?

300
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:01,560
Why did The One end
our employment contract all of a sudden?

301
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:03,360
Yeah, Boss.

302
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:06,120
We've worked so well together with them.

303
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:09,200
Plus, we're launching a promotion
for the campaign for couples.

304
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:11,800
Can they really end our contract
just like that?

305
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:13,720
Yeah, is it even doable, Boss?

306
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:16,080
- Technically, a contract that--
- Calm down, everyone.

307
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:18,840
I'm not sure what happened either.

308
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,480
I think it's because…

309
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:29,480
Mr. Thee wouldn't marry Ms. Bella,
so Mrs. Anna got very angry.

310
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:35,280
Then that means he chose you!

311
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,680
He's so awesome!

312
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:44,160
Before you praise him,
you should feel sorry for yourself.

313
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:48,000
Didn't this happen because he went
against his dear mother?

314
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:51,720
That's why she declared war on us
by ending the contract!

315
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:54,640
What? It's a personal matter.
How is it related to the contract?

316
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:59,520
Mrs. Anna is going after Mook
in every way she can.

317
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:02,280
After that heavy blow from Mr. Thee,

318
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:05,200
of course, she'd hit us back
with this lightning-fast order!

319
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:10,120
I'm sorry for getting
our company into trouble, Boss.

320
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:13,920
I'll take responsibility for this.

321
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,160
Why?

322
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,480
Why should you be responsible for it?

323
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:20,280
It's not like our company
did a bad job or anything.

324
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:24,000
She's right, Mook. I agree with Whan.

325
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:25,880
This isn't your fault.

326
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:29,720
Yeah, haters are gonna hate,
even if you were a saint.

327
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:30,800
Don't let them win!

328
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:37,480
Mook, so what did Mr. Thee say?

329
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,400
Have you talked to him?

330
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,040
She has coronary artery disease.

331
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:57,280
We'd better perform
a bypass surgery on her right away.

332
00:32:57,360 --> 00:33:00,280
This means we'll attach grafts
to supply the heart muscle

333
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:04,520
to create a detour that allows
enough blood to be supplied to the heart.

334
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:08,600
It is done to prevent heart failure
due to reduced blood flow to the heart.

335
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:12,640
- But I still don't--
- Can you perform it now, Doctor?

336
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:16,320
I want my mom to get better
as soon as possible.

337
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:20,400
Sure. I'll proceed with the treatment
as soon as possible.

338
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,440
Thank you.

339
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:39,880
Mom,

340
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:43,440
please agree to do what the doctor said.

341
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:46,280
From now on,

342
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:50,400
I'll take care of you.

343
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,640
- Mom.
- Yes?

344
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:11,239
Before you found out,
did you recognize me?

345
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,560
I wasn't sure,

346
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:20,199
but I could tell
by the look you'd give me,

347
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,159
there's just something about it.

348
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:29,040
Have you and your brother been happy?

349
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,920
Have you been doing well all this time?

350
00:34:34,080 --> 00:34:35,679
Let's go, Tawan. Come on.

351
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:39,440
- My toy car!
- Tawan!

352
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,520
Saifah, help me!

353
00:34:46,600 --> 00:34:49,199
- There's a fire! Come on. Come here!
- Please help my brother!

354
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:52,280
Saifah, don't leave me!

355
00:34:56,639 --> 00:35:01,040
The family who adopted me
has taken good care of me.

356
00:35:04,680 --> 00:35:08,840
When I recovered, I went back to our home.

357
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:12,400
I was heartbroken
that I didn't find you both there.

358
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:16,720
If it weren't for Ms. Mook,
I would've never gotten to see you.

359
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,000
Please don't worry, Mom.

360
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:27,600
I won't leave you ever again.

361
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:32,640
We'll get to be together from now on.

362
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:36,000
Okay.

363
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:40,880
What about Ms. Mook?

364
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:44,160
Something came up at work,
so she had to rush to a meeting.

365
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:49,160
I meant, what will you do
about your fiancée and Mook?

366
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:00,240
Calm down, Mook.

367
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:03,520
I think Mr. Thee
has already thought it through,

368
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:05,160
with everything that's happened.

369
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:12,800
And I knew something like this
would happen to our company.

370
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:17,920
What do you mean? You knew?

371
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:26,320
<i>But you two are engaged.</i>

372
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:29,600
You'll have to get married anyway, right?

373
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:31,840
I won't do it.

374
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:38,360
And I'm not worried at all

375
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:41,760
because Bell will get to meet someone good

376
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:47,080
who can really love her and protect her.

377
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:50,760
But I'm sure Mrs. Anna
won't let you off easy.

378
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:57,720
I'm going to tell my mother

379
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:00,080
that I won't marry anyone

380
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:03,320
other than Mook.

381
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:07,520
Are you sure about this, Mr. Thee?

382
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:14,000
She's the woman I love.

383
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,680
<i>Did he really say that?</i>

384
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:33,520
He made things very clear.

385
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:36,680
What about you? How do you feel?

386
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,880
Is Ms. Mook here?

387
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,440
What?

388
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,760
After that termination email you sent,
what do you need her for?

389
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,520
I need to talk to her
about something urgent.

390
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:34,600
- What? Wait! Come on. Stop her!
- Let's keep things civil!

391
00:38:34,680 --> 00:38:35,720
Hey!

392
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:41,440
Please calm down.

393
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:44,120
Let's keep it civil here.

394
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:47,120
- Ms. Bell?
- Ms. Mook.

395
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:51,120
Do you know where Thee is?

396
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:54,760
What happened?

397
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:58,040
Yesterday he had a big fight
with Aunt Anna,

398
00:38:58,120 --> 00:39:00,640
and no one can get ahold of him today.

399
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:04,200
So, do you know where he is?

400
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,920
So, he got to meet his real mom?

401
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,080
Hold on.

402
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:19,960
Mr. Thee isn't Mrs. Anna's son
but Ms. Narin's son?

403
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:25,600
Yes, I just found out not long ago too.

404
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:29,880
All I knew was that Mrs. Anna adopted him,

405
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:32,160
but she's never allowed anyone
to talk about it.

406
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:37,680
Anyway, we should hurry and find him.

407
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:40,200
Aunt Anna announced that
she'd scale back Thee's role at TJ Group,

408
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,720
and she's taking away his CEO title too.

409
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:48,480
You want my son so badly, don't you?

410
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:53,200
Fine. You can have him.

411
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:59,720
But you can only take him
and not TJ Group's assets.

412
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:10,880
I'm sure Mr. Thee was already prepared
for this to happen.

413
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:39,360
What the heck?

414
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,800
Yeah, May. What's going on?

415
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,880
Mr. Thee's fiancée isn't mad at Mook,

416
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:45,960
and she seems really close to our boss.

417
00:40:46,680 --> 00:40:49,000
What exactly happened? I'm so confused.

418
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:50,760
Those two must be close for sure.

419
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:53,680
There must be something we don't know.

420
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:59,360
But what I do know
is we'd better find new clients.

421
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:02,320
Mrs. Anna seems like someone
who keeps her word.

422
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,960
We're getting axed for sure.

423
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:07,120
- Yeah, I agree.
- Yeah.

424
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:10,800
If you agree, then please scatter
and go back to work. Go ahead.

425
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:13,240
- Shall we? Let's go.
- Yeah.

426
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,960
- It's locked.
- It opens that way.

427
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,400
- Let's go.
- Got it, got it.

428
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:34,640
See, Kuk? I told you Mrs. Anna
could really handle it for us.

429
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:38,120
She already gave orders
to end A Round Trip's contract too.

430
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,440
And Mr. Thee's fine with it?

431
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:43,600
That's got nothing to do with us.

432
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:45,800
But they emailed them an official letter.

433
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:47,920
That means Mrs. Anna is serious.

434
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:53,920
You know, she gave us
so many opportunities.

435
00:41:54,520 --> 00:41:58,080
She gave us a new project,
and she also got rid of our competitor.

436
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,920
That's why we have to give it our all

437
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:04,760
to show Mrs. Anna
how well-prepared we are.

438
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:17,800
You know, you didn't have to drive me.

439
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:22,520
Are you okay?

440
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:28,080
With how Mr. Thee won't marry you, I mean.

441
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:30,920
Of course I am.

442
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,200
In fact, I'm happy

443
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:36,280
that he's brave enough
to decide to do what he wants

444
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:39,040
without worrying
about the problems he'll face.

445
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:44,360
What about you?

446
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,320
Are you afraid of the problems
that'll result from this?

447
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,440
I've been running away from my problems.

448
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:55,400
I did whatever my dad wanted,
even if I was reluctant.

449
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:59,040
Thee's paved the way for me.

450
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:02,440
Now it's up to me to handle things myself.

451
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:06,600
Me too.

452
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,480
I meant between me and Prao.

453
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:14,480
We've been having problems for so long.

454
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:20,280
It's time we admitted it
and find a solution for our son.

455
00:43:23,520 --> 00:43:25,240
Good luck.

456
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:29,560
Thank you.

457
00:43:40,960 --> 00:43:42,600
NEW MESSAGE

458
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:48,600
I won an award
for the new collection I designed!

459
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:04,920
- I'm good, right?
- You rock.

460
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:20,760
- Great job.
- Thank you.

461
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:41,480
Mr. Thee, why don't you come inside?

462
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:46,120
I shouldn't. I don't want to bother you.

463
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:51,600
Plus, your mom said
she didn't want me to come here again.

464
00:44:56,000 --> 00:45:00,640
So, how's Ms. Narin holding up?

465
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:04,160
The doctor will set a date
for the bypass surgery,

466
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:08,040
but we may have to wait
for her to feel more ready.

467
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:19,400
I'm… so sorry

468
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:23,080
about your brother.

469
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,080
It was my fault.

470
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:37,000
If I'd tried harder to save him…

471
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:40,960
my brother…

472
00:45:46,360 --> 00:45:47,600
would've survived.

473
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:11,560
It's not your fault at all.

474
00:46:14,120 --> 00:46:16,360
No one would want it to happen.

475
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:20,960
Please don't blame yourself.

476
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:37,560
But I don't know
how to break it to my mom.

477
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:45,120
I don't want her condition
to get any worse.

478
00:47:01,640 --> 00:47:03,840
It won't be too late to tell her

479
00:47:04,920 --> 00:47:06,720
when she gets better.

480
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:16,640
I'm sure she's strong enough
to get through it.

481
00:48:00,480 --> 00:48:03,360
I knew Mom would do this.

482
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:07,440
Mr. Thee, please just apologize
to Mrs. Anna,

483
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:09,720
before everything gets worse.

484
00:48:10,720 --> 00:48:13,120
Mr. Joe seems very angry too.

485
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:16,480
He might pull out of the project.

486
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:18,480
But Bell and I don't love each other.

487
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:23,160
And we both have someone we love.

488
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:27,360
Mrs. Anna already gave orders to end
the contract with A Round Trip Travel.

489
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:29,880
I'll try talking to her.

490
00:48:29,960 --> 00:48:31,960
There's no use, Mr. Thee.

491
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:35,720
Mrs. Anna will do anything
to win against you

492
00:48:35,800 --> 00:48:38,120
unless you do what she says.

493
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:45,120
I've met my mom.

494
00:48:45,960 --> 00:48:47,200
What?

495
00:48:49,040 --> 00:48:51,720
Ms. Narin is my real mom, Mr. Pitak.

496
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:59,240
I already got back what I value the most.

497
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:05,640
I don't need much more.

498
00:49:11,400 --> 00:49:12,680
Your mom?

499
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:18,840
What are you talking about?

500
00:49:19,760 --> 00:49:22,960
How could an orphan like you have a mom?

501
00:49:34,200 --> 00:49:36,600
Thank you for visiting me, Chadchai.

502
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,000
How's the hotel?

503
00:49:43,440 --> 00:49:45,600
Please get plenty of rest
and get well soon.

504
00:49:45,680 --> 00:49:47,480
Don't worry about work at the hotel.

505
00:49:53,480 --> 00:49:55,480
What's wrong, Chadchai?

506
00:49:57,320 --> 00:50:00,400
The One has made a change.

507
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:02,280
There's some kind of problem
with Mr. Thee.

508
00:50:02,960 --> 00:50:06,520
I don't know if it'll affect our hotel.

509
00:50:06,600 --> 00:50:09,640
Why? What's the problem with Mr. Thee?

510
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:14,520
So you've been looking for your mom
all this time?

511
00:50:20,440 --> 00:50:21,960
Mom, I'm sorry

512
00:50:23,360 --> 00:50:25,360
for not telling you about it before.

513
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:26,800
So what will you do now?

514
00:50:27,560 --> 00:50:28,840
You'd better think it through.

515
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:34,680
Do you want to be the CEO of TJ Group
or a nobody, like before?

516
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:37,320
That's unrelated, though.

517
00:50:38,560 --> 00:50:40,160
Even though I've met my mom,

518
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:44,000
I never thought of leaving you.

519
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:48,160
No! You have no choice
but to be someone I've created,

520
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:51,960
and I'm the only mother you can have.

521
00:50:56,400 --> 00:51:01,400
Do as I say. Marry Bell,
so everything can go back to normal.

522
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:07,720
As for your mom,
just go your separate ways.

523
00:51:07,800 --> 00:51:10,120
Consider her dead.

524
00:51:12,520 --> 00:51:14,000
I can't do that.

525
00:51:16,120 --> 00:51:20,560
I know how much I really owe you,

526
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:25,880
but you're making me leave my real mom.

527
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,400
I can't do that.

528
00:51:29,480 --> 00:51:31,160
Try me, then!

529
00:51:31,240 --> 00:51:34,440
You'll learn what I'm capable of doing

530
00:51:35,280 --> 00:51:39,080
about your mom and Veluree!

531
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:31,040
From what I heard,

532
00:52:32,160 --> 00:52:36,000
there's been an order
to remove Mr. Thee's CEO title.

533
00:52:37,880 --> 00:52:40,280
Ms. Narin. Ms. Narin.

534
00:52:40,880 --> 00:52:42,360
Ms. Narin!

535
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:50,560
Nurse! Nurse! Please be okay, Ms. Narin.

536
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:54,120
Ms. Narin! Nurse! Please come take a look!

537
00:52:56,040 --> 00:52:58,280
Nurse! Please take a look at her.

538
00:53:05,120 --> 00:53:06,200
I'll go get the doctor.

539
00:53:26,320 --> 00:53:27,240
Bell.

540
00:53:27,320 --> 00:53:30,920
Thee? Where have you been?

541
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:33,440
You know Aunt Anna's
really mad at you, right?

542
00:53:35,360 --> 00:53:38,000
Have I gotten you into trouble too?

543
00:53:38,800 --> 00:53:39,840
Not at all.

544
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:43,280
I knew this would happen someday,
so don't worry.

545
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:48,920
Ms. Mook told me you've met your real mom?

546
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:54,440
Yes, I've talked things out with her.

547
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:57,000
But it was almost too late.

548
00:53:58,520 --> 00:53:59,960
What do you mean?

549
00:54:03,520 --> 00:54:04,920
Just a second, Bell.

550
00:54:09,520 --> 00:54:13,120
Yes, Mr. Chadchai?
About Ms. Narin's removal, I--

551
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:18,680
Okay. I'll be right over.

552
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:21,680
Bell, I'll talk to you later.

553
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:34,800
I took a look at our year plan.

554
00:54:34,880 --> 00:54:37,320
Because our contract was terminated,

555
00:54:38,040 --> 00:54:40,640
we'll need to find
at least 30% more clients

556
00:54:40,720 --> 00:54:42,880
to offset the loss.

557
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:48,840
Together, I think we can pull it off.

558
00:54:50,840 --> 00:54:53,600
Don't worry. I trust that we can.

559
00:54:54,640 --> 00:54:56,920
But I think Mrs. Anna
was wrong about this.

560
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:00,000
Come again?

561
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:02,280
Why should we give in, Boss?

562
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:05,160
You've said it yourself.
We did our job perfectly well.

563
00:55:05,800 --> 00:55:08,640
She needs to separate
her work and personal life.

564
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:12,160
So what will you do?

565
00:55:15,800 --> 00:55:17,200
We need to negotiate.

566
00:55:17,840 --> 00:55:20,960
But if that doesn't work,
we still have a legitimate contract.

567
00:55:21,560 --> 00:55:23,400
We'll have to take legal action.

568
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:29,640
MR. THEE

569
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:33,080
Yes, Mr. Thee?

570
00:55:35,680 --> 00:55:37,680
Okay, I'll be right over!

571
00:55:38,320 --> 00:55:39,320
What happened, Mook?

572
00:55:39,400 --> 00:55:41,200
Ms. Narin is getting an emergency surgery.

573
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:43,000
I have to go, Boss.

574
00:55:43,080 --> 00:55:44,920
- Can I come too?
- Sure.

575
00:55:51,920 --> 00:55:53,720
Mom, I'm sorry…

576
00:55:57,120 --> 00:55:59,040
…that I wasn't upfront with you.

577
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:05,560
I was afraid that if I told you,
your condition would get worse.

578
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:07,680
Who taught you to say that?!

579
00:56:07,760 --> 00:56:08,840
But it's true!

580
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:11,560
You and Dad always fight
whenever you meet.

581
00:56:11,640 --> 00:56:15,240
You're so heartless! I hate you, Mommy!

582
00:56:20,760 --> 00:56:23,920
Mook. Do you remember?

583
00:56:25,160 --> 00:56:27,440
I asked you to have faith in my love.

584
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:31,960
I've proven it to you, see?

585
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:29,720
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
